## Finding a Specific Image Policy

When troubleshooting or checking the status of a specific application's image automation, you can filter the image policies using `grep`.

<%= warning_text('Image policies can only be queried on PTL (Production-like) clusters for both CFT and SDS environments.') %>

### CFT PTL Cluster

Connect to the CFT PTL cluster:

```bash
az aks get-credentials --resource-group cft-ptl-00-rg --name cft-ptl-00-aks --subscription DCD-CFTAPPS-STG --overwrite
```

Search for a specific image policy:

```bash
kubectl get imagepolicy.image.toolkit.fluxcd.io -n flux-system | grep <application-name>
```

**Example output:**

```
toffee-frontend                                     sdshmctspublic.azurecr.io/toffee/frontend                         prod-f8bc08c-20250225100311      True    Latest image tag for sdshmctspublic.azurecr.io/toffee/frontend resolved to prod-f8bc08c-20250225100311
```

The output shows:
- **Policy name**: `toffee-frontend`
- **Image repository**: `sdshmctspublic.azurecr.io/toffee/frontend`
- **Latest image tag**: `prod-f8bc08c-20250225100311`
- **Status**: `True` (working correctly)
- **Message**: Confirmation that the image has been resolved

### SDS PTL Cluster

Connect to the SDS PTL cluster:

```bash
az aks get-credentials --resource-group ss-ptl-00-rg --name ss-ptl-00-aks --subscription DTS-SHAREDSERVICES-STG --overwrite
```

Search for a specific image policy using the same command:

```bash
kubectl get imagepolicy.image.toolkit.fluxcd.io -n flux-system | grep <application-name>
```

